features: Value Pack: 3 pack delicate spiral notebooks with 80 gsm paper and 75 sheets/150 pages each are suitable for recording your tasks, notes, and ideas, making work management more efficient.

Floral Subject Design: The aesthetic notebook has a sturdy cover and features a cute floral design, fresh and harmonious colors, adding a touch of charm and personality to your daily writing, and these cute notebooks with nice quality paper and good ring binding make a nice gift.

Two-Spiral Binding: The notebook journal has sturdy 2- spiral bounding that makes it easier to fold over the page or divide the notebook into sections, 80gsm thick paper withstands ink bleed-through, giving you a good writing experience.

Mini Size: Small A5 notebook measures 8.3 inches (21 cm) length x 5.8 inches (14.7 cm) wide and easily fits in purses, backpacks, and travel bags and 8mm ruled pages are suitable for note taking and journaling.

Multiple Uses: The college ruled notebooks can be applied to studying, work recording, creative writing, painting, and diary. As an ideal choice for offices, schools, and households, spiral note books are perfect gifts for friends, families, classmates, and workmates as well.

reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars lovely prints, nice paper
reviews.reviewText: these notebooks are a nice size, with a soft off-white or pale cream colored paper. the paper is thin, but not overly so. some wetter inks might bleed through, and darker inks will lightly ghost on the opposite side of the page.the covers are lovely, but i wouldn't call them a hard cover. they're flexible and fairly sturdy, though, and the prints are well done.the binding is sturdy, and the pages and covers flip smoothly. i like the little space for the date and page number. if you like numbered pages like i do, but also occasionally tear pages out, no one would be the wiser! and the pages do tear out fairly easily when you're specifically trying to tear them out, but are sturdy enough to not just rip out if you look at them sideways.overall, nice little notebooks for the price! i just wish the paper was a wee bit thicker, as i like to use wetter and darker inks.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Express yourself with pen and ink
reviews.reviewText: These three spiral notebooks have pretty "Garden Blooms" covers of a heavy card stock. The gold-colored spiral spine has large loops, so the notebook doesn't only lie flat, it can easily do a 360 and concentrate on just one page. If you're keeping a dream journal or if ideas come to you in the middle of the night, this notebook is the right size to keep on your nightstand. And the spiral is big enough to slip in my favorite pen.The height is 8.25 inches and each page is a hair over 5.75 inches. (Size A5 for those in the stationary realm.) The lines are ruled at 5/16 of an inch. Each page has a place to note the date and page number.The 75 pages (2-sided, so 150 pages to write on) are a creamy color, high quality, and of a decent weight. There is a very slight crease at the far edge of every page. The crease makes it easier to fold over the page, maybe to mark a special note, or divide the notebook into sections.There are as many uses for a good-quality, easy to carry notebook as there are people who need to keep track of things, like recipes, gift ideas, party planning, etc. Let me grab my new notebook and make a list...
